Hi,

I'm from Northern NJ, and work as a developer in NYC. Like some others, this is my last class in the program. I'm officially specializing in ML but will also have completed the needed course work for the Computational perception and Robotics specialization. I admit I'm a bit afraid of this class as I've never quite been strong with proofs. Hoping all goes well for all this semester.

ML will have you running ML algorithms over datasets and writing about it (10+ pages). You can use whatever code/programs you can beg, borrow or steal to do your report analysis. The four reports and 2 exams are your only grade.

ML4T will have you writing your own algorithms, with a focus on time series data. You'll use a lot of python and pandas, and learn a little bit about the stock market. It is a gentler introduction to ML topics, but you won't get quite the depth you would in ML.
